org.jdbdt

Class DataSetBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jdbdt.DataSetBuilder

  • public final class DataSetBuilder
extends Object
    Data set builder.

    Objects of this kind provide a convenient manner to define data sets programmatically.

    Data builders can be used as follows:

    • They are created with calls to either JDBDT.builder(DataSource), to create a fresh data set, or to DataSet.build() to add data to an existing data set.
    • Entries (rows) in the data set are specified by setting one column filler (ColumnFiller instance) per each column in the table, using the set(String, ColumnFiller) base method or one of several convenience methods e.g., the ones available for sequence or pseudo-random values.
    • Each call to generate(int) causes a specified number of rows to be added to the underlying data set, in line with the current column fillers set.
    • The data set instance for a builder can be retrieved using data().
    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    JDBDT.builder(DataSource), DataSet.build()

      • sequence

        public <T> DataSetBuilder sequence(String column,
                                   T initial,
                                   Function<T,T> step)
        Set a sequence filler using a step-function.

        The sequence of values generated by the filler starts with the specified initial value, and subsequent values are generated using the step function which takes as input the previous value. The sequence will then be s(0), s(1), ... where s(0) = initial and s(n+1) = step.apply(s(n)) for all n >= 0 .

        Type Parameters:
        T - Column datum type.
        Parameters:
        column - Column name.
        initial - Initial value.
        step - Step function.
        Returns:
        The builder instance (for chained calls).
        See Also:
        sequence(String, Function)

      • sequence

        public DataSetBuilder sequence(String column,
                               Function<Integer,?> step,
                               int initial)
        Set sequence filler using a index-based step-function.

        The sequence of values generated by the filler starts with the specified initial value, and subsequent values are generated using the step function which takes as input the index of the row being generated, starting from the initial value. The sequence will then be s(start), s(start+1), ... where s(i) = step.apply(i) for all i >= start.

        Parameters:
        column - Column name.
        step - Step function.
        initial - Initial value fed to step function.
        Returns:
        The builder instance (for chained calls).
        See Also:
        sequence(String, Object, Function)

      • random

        public DataSetBuilder random(String column,
                             Function<Random,?> gen)
        Set customized random filler.

        The specified column will be filled with values that are obtained from a generator function. The generator function takes a Random instance as an argument and returns a value: it should use the generator to produce column values in deterministic fashion (in particular, the random number generator argument should not be re-seeded).

        Illustration of use

        The filler below will yield strings "ID_0", ..., "ID_9" with an uniform distribution:

         DataSet ds = ...;
 ...
 ds.random("SomeColumn", rng -> "ID_" + rng.nextInt(10));
        Parameters:
        column - Column name.
        gen - Generator function.
        Returns:
        The builder instance (for chained calls).
        See Also:
        Random, random(String, int, int), random(String, long, long), random(String, float, float), random(String, double, double), random(String, Date, Date), random(String, Time, Time), random(String, Timestamp, Timestamp)
